1
00:00:10,960 --> 00:00:13,420
♪The maple mark on your skin♪

2
00:00:14,230 --> 00:00:17,040
♪The only proof we exist♪

3
00:00:18,210 --> 00:00:21,450
♪I stole you back from destiny♪

4
00:00:21,560 --> 00:00:24,430
♪But can I redeem myself♪

5
00:00:24,430 --> 00:00:26,540
♪I don't care what fate foretells♪

6
00:00:26,750 --> 00:00:30,330
♪Or how rough the road may be♪

7
00:00:30,340 --> 00:00:33,280
♪Stay, I'll fight for you♪

8
00:00:33,610 --> 00:00:37,660
♪That's all I'll ever do♪

9
00:00:37,760 --> 00:00:39,890
♪If life is just a show♪

10
00:00:39,890 --> 00:00:42,650
♪I'll stay with you till the end♪

11
00:00:42,650 --> 00:00:44,980
♪I'm scared we'll wake up alone♪

12
00:00:44,980 --> 00:00:47,960
♪So don't let this dream end♪

13
00:00:47,960 --> 00:00:52,420
♪In my bones, in my heart♪

14
00:00:52,420 --> 00:00:54,100
♪I know I'll have to leave♪

15
00:00:54,100 --> 00:00:55,670
♪You must not leave my side♪

16
00:00:55,670 --> 00:00:57,260
♪No place can hold us in♪

17
00:00:57,260 --> 00:01:01,910
♪Not when it's you and me♪

18
00:01:06,890 --> 00:01:10,400
♪Forever♪

19
00:01:11,490 --> 00:01:15,250
♪In my soul♪

20
00:01:17,260 --> 00:01:23,300
=This Palace Maid Isn't Very Calm=
=Episode 3=

21
00:01:29,790 --> 00:01:30,640
Mother,

22
00:01:30,650 --> 00:01:31,680
why aren't you eating?

23
00:01:32,120 --> 00:01:33,590
It's all so bland.

24
00:01:35,950 --> 00:01:37,920
Everything I eat tastes like water.

25
00:01:38,120 --> 00:01:40,230
I just tried this tofu.

26
00:01:40,590 --> 00:01:42,000
I didn't think it was bland.

27
00:01:42,430 --> 00:01:43,510
You only

28
00:01:44,310 --> 00:01:46,120
dine with me once in a while,

29
00:01:46,590 --> 00:01:48,590
of course it feels fresh and tasty.

30
00:01:48,950 --> 00:01:50,310
But me?

31
00:01:50,350 --> 00:01:52,310
I eat this every single day.

32
00:01:53,870 --> 00:01:55,000
I don't even know

33
00:01:55,310 --> 00:01:57,150
when this will end.

34
00:01:57,310 --> 00:01:58,200
Mother...

35
00:01:58,510 --> 00:01:59,430
Your Highness.

36
00:01:59,430 --> 00:02:01,350
The kitchen sent over some snacks.

37
00:02:01,790 --> 00:02:03,790
They have a new cook

38
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:06,150
who can make sugar-free snacks

39
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:08,000
for people with diabetes.

40
00:02:09,870 --> 00:02:10,710
Bring her in.

41
00:02:15,910 --> 00:02:17,280
Greetings,

42
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:18,280
Your Highnesses.

43
00:02:18,870 --> 00:02:21,120
You're the new cook?

44
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:22,240
I am.

45
00:02:22,260 --> 00:02:22,940
You may rise.

46
00:02:22,940 --> 00:02:24,020
Thank you, Your Highness.

47
00:02:25,870 --> 00:02:26,840
Are you sure

48
00:02:28,310 --> 00:02:29,400
these snacks are safe

49
00:02:29,750 --> 00:02:31,750
for a diabetic?

50
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:32,840
Absolutely.

51
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:35,080
Don't worry, Your Highness.

52
00:02:35,240 --> 00:02:37,710
I used all-natural ingredients

53
00:02:37,710 --> 00:02:39,400
that won't spike your blood sugar.

54
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:40,750
No sugar at all.

55
00:02:40,750 --> 00:02:41,590
Well…

56
00:02:41,590 --> 00:02:42,480
That said,

57
00:02:42,480 --> 00:02:43,680
they're still desserts,

58
00:02:43,710 --> 00:02:45,280
so you shouldn't eat too much at once.

59
00:02:45,560 --> 00:02:47,520
But if you're craving something sweet,

60
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:48,910
a little is perfectly fine.

61
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:49,960
Mother,

62
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:51,120
give it a try.

63
00:02:59,310 --> 00:03:00,360
Tasty.

64
00:03:00,360 --> 00:03:01,200
I like it.

65
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:02,960
Reward her.

66
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:06,310
Thank you, Your Highness.

67
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:12,430
She was rewarded.

68
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:21,800
Your Highness,

69
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:23,560
the key to managing diabetes

70
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:24,870
isn't just diet.

71
00:03:24,870 --> 00:03:25,800
It's also exercise.

72
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:26,680
Exercise?

73
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:27,520
Mm.

74
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:30,360
I have a leg condition.

75
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:32,310
Moving around is difficult.

76
00:03:32,310 --> 00:03:34,590
We won't be doing anything like walking.

77
00:03:34,590 --> 00:03:36,840
Today, we're trying something new.

78
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:37,870
In my hometown,

79
00:03:37,870 --> 00:03:40,080
we have a blood-circulating exercise

80
00:03:40,080 --> 00:03:42,030
called radio calisthenics.

81
00:03:42,190 --> 00:03:43,750
Watch closely. Before we start,

82
00:03:43,750 --> 00:03:45,000
just march in place.

83
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:46,360
One, two, three, four,

84
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:49,030
five, six, seven, eight.

85
00:03:49,430 --> 00:03:51,590
First set, chest expansion.

86
00:03:52,030 --> 00:03:53,680
One, two, three, four,

87
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:55,470
five, six, seven, eight.

88
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:57,250
It's that simple.

89
00:03:57,260 --> 00:03:58,120
Come on.

90
00:03:58,120 --> 00:03:59,120
Let's try it.

91
00:04:00,360 --> 00:04:01,320
- Be careful.
- Well…

92
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:03,710
I'll give it a try.

93
00:04:04,030 --> 00:04:05,960
Let's start by marching in place.

94
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:06,800
Get moving.

95
00:04:07,120 --> 00:04:09,430
One, two, three, four,

96
00:04:09,430 --> 00:04:11,080
five, six, seven...

97
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:12,150
Is Ye Jin

98
00:04:12,150 --> 00:04:13,590
losing her mind?

99
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:28,560
Food works the same way.

100
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:31,310
Healthy and delicious
don't have to conflict.

101
00:04:31,630 --> 00:04:33,070
How so?

102
00:04:33,070 --> 00:04:34,310
With diabetes,

103
00:04:34,310 --> 00:04:35,680
you should avoid greasy food,

104
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:38,630
but that doesn't mean
no meat at all.

105
00:04:38,630 --> 00:04:40,720
In fact, a moderate amount

106
00:04:40,720 --> 00:04:42,270
is good for the body

107
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:43,750
and helps the condition.

108
00:04:44,310 --> 00:04:45,430
My ancestors...

109
00:04:49,270 --> 00:04:52,510
My family studied this illness extensively.

110
00:04:52,510 --> 00:04:54,680
I know several recipes

111
00:04:54,830 --> 00:04:56,510
that I'd like to share with Your Highness.

112
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:02,720
I have to say,

113
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:04,510
after moving around a bit,

114
00:05:04,870 --> 00:05:07,000
I do feel refreshed.

115
00:05:07,510 --> 00:05:09,510
That was just the appetizer.

116
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:12,720
I've got plenty more tricks.

117
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:13,570
Let's keep going.

118
00:05:13,590 --> 00:05:14,720
All right.

119
00:05:17,190 --> 00:05:18,640
- She has truly
- Is that okay?

120
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:19,870
won her over.

121
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:24,860
Enjoy, Your Highness.

122
00:05:33,510 --> 00:05:35,870
Whether or not it helps the illness,

123
00:05:36,390 --> 00:05:37,430
the taste alone

124
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:39,560
suits me.

125
00:05:39,560 --> 00:05:40,400
Reward her.

126
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:44,000
Thank you, Your Highness.

127
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:47,560
(I've read the novel.)

128
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:49,190
(Of course I know your taste.)

129
00:05:53,630 --> 00:05:56,120
Life on cheat mode really hits different.

130
00:05:56,210 --> 00:05:57,070
Next,

131
00:05:57,070 --> 00:05:58,390
I'll use something called

132
00:05:58,390 --> 00:06:00,480
Thai pressure therapy.

133
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:09,120
Way better than those physicians

134
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:10,750
at the Imperial Clinic.

135
00:06:11,390 --> 00:06:12,230
Ye Jin,

136
00:06:12,510 --> 00:06:14,630
you are so thoughtful.

137
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:15,760
Reward her.

138
00:06:21,070 --> 00:06:22,720
As great as this is,

139
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:24,480
it's not the real world.

140
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:27,040
I still need to find a way back.

141
00:06:43,510 --> 00:06:45,950
Your Highness, if we don't go now,
we never will.

142
00:07:08,270 --> 00:07:09,270
I swear

143
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:12,600
to hold this ground.

144
00:07:13,190 --> 00:07:14,950
I will not retreat.

145
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:36,750
Your Highness, you had another nightmare.

146
00:07:39,070 --> 00:07:40,190
Seven years.

147
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:43,160
Still the same dream.

148
00:08:01,560 --> 00:08:04,270
This gate looks so familiar.

149
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:12,600
I wonder if my transmigration

150
00:08:13,310 --> 00:08:15,390
is linked to this gate.

151
00:09:13,390 --> 00:09:14,320
One last look.

152
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:15,320
Just one last look.

153
00:09:16,720 --> 00:09:18,750
I need to confirm

154
00:09:19,270 --> 00:09:21,510
if that birthmark is actually there.

155
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:27,040
Who's there?

156
00:09:27,550 --> 00:09:28,390
Stay right there.

157
00:09:33,790 --> 00:09:34,630
It's you.

158
00:09:36,550 --> 00:09:37,510
I didn't see anything.

159
00:09:40,910 --> 00:09:42,000
Why are you here?

160
00:09:42,510 --> 00:09:43,350
I...

161
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:44,240
I...

162
00:09:44,240 --> 00:09:45,480
Why am I here?

163
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:46,960
You think I want to be here?

164
00:09:47,030 --> 00:09:48,160
If I wasn't looking for a bug

165
00:09:48,160 --> 00:09:49,120
or the portal back,

166
00:09:49,120 --> 00:09:50,870
why would I be here in the scorching sun?

167
00:09:51,080 --> 00:09:52,080
Am I crazy?

168
00:09:52,190 --> 00:09:53,030
Seriously.

169
00:09:53,120 --> 00:09:53,960
A bug?

170
00:09:54,750 --> 00:09:55,590
What does that mean?

171
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:57,870
And what is a portal?

172
00:09:59,030 --> 00:10:01,240
You can hear me?

173
00:10:01,730 --> 00:10:02,590
Of course.

174
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:03,750
I'm not deaf.

175
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:05,060
(Aren't my OOC lines)

176
00:10:05,060 --> 00:10:06,080
(supposed to be blocked?)

177
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:07,040
(The lead didn't react,)

178
00:10:07,040 --> 00:10:08,080
(why can he hear me?)

179
00:10:12,270 --> 00:10:13,320
Give it back.

180
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:14,840
Give it back.

181
00:10:16,080 --> 00:10:16,930
Give it back.

182
00:10:17,030 --> 00:10:17,870
I...

183
00:10:22,840 --> 00:10:23,870
Give it back.

184
00:10:28,360 --> 00:10:29,670
Give it back.

185
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:32,390
Give it back.

186
00:11:08,420 --> 00:11:09,270
Your Highness.

187
00:11:09,270 --> 00:11:10,180
She…

188
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:11,960
How did she get here?

189
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:14,390
Why asking me?

190
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:17,670
How should I know?

191
00:11:18,630 --> 00:11:19,480
First, she claims

192
00:11:19,750 --> 00:11:21,840
she's pregnant with your child.

193
00:11:22,150 --> 00:11:23,510
Then she talks nonsense

194
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:25,870
and hits on you.

195
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:27,030
And now?

196
00:11:27,030 --> 00:11:28,240
She actually kissed you.

197
00:11:28,510 --> 00:11:29,440
Unbelievable.

198
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:30,510
I have never seen

199
00:11:30,510 --> 00:11:32,550
such a bold maid in my life.

200
00:11:35,150 --> 00:11:36,150
Bold.

201
00:11:37,150 --> 00:11:37,990
Indeed.

202
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:47,120
That was too close.

203
00:11:47,550 --> 00:11:48,720
I almost got caught.

204
00:11:49,270 --> 00:11:50,480
Thank god I'm quick-witted.

205
00:11:51,150 --> 00:11:52,550
A kiss solved the crisis.

206
00:11:54,390 --> 00:11:55,870
It's just a shame my first kiss

207
00:11:55,870 --> 00:11:57,150
went to a fictional character.

208
00:11:58,390 --> 00:11:59,840
I've been with you since I was a kid.

209
00:12:00,080 --> 00:12:02,670
I know you hate social climbers.

210
00:12:03,150 --> 00:12:04,200
But with Ye Jin,

211
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:06,600
why do you just let her mess around?

212
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:08,520
If the Empress Dowager hears about this,

213
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:10,670
it'll cause more trouble.

214
00:12:11,540 --> 00:12:13,080
Doesn't that make it more interesting?

215
00:12:20,580 --> 00:12:22,140
("Once an Empress")

216
00:12:22,150 --> 00:12:23,200
This gate

217
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:25,440
is exactly the same as the one on the poster.

218
00:12:34,820 --> 00:12:37,260
♪I am but an outsider♪

219
00:12:37,300 --> 00:12:39,460
♪Yet something drags me deeper♪

220
00:12:39,700 --> 00:12:43,740
♪Outwit the world but not the way we meet♪

221
00:12:43,740 --> 00:12:47,980
♪Splendid blooms line deadly ground♪

222
00:12:52,260 --> 00:12:55,500
♪Life's a phantom, yet I find you♪

223
00:12:55,660 --> 00:12:59,060
♪In a world of lies, you're all that's clear♪

224
00:12:59,060 --> 00:13:01,580
♪I know how this story ends♪

225
00:13:01,580 --> 00:13:06,140
♪I still want what's in your eyes♪

226
00:13:06,460 --> 00:13:10,580
♪Truth or lie—I can't tell♪

227
00:13:15,540 --> 00:13:18,860
♪You hide it all behind your lines♪

228
00:13:18,860 --> 00:13:22,140
♪So familiar, yet out of reach♪

229
00:13:22,340 --> 00:13:25,420
♪A history that no one can search♪

230
00:13:25,660 --> 00:13:28,940
♪Like you drift in from another star♪

231
00:13:28,980 --> 00:13:30,740
♪I am but an outsider♪

232
00:13:30,740 --> 00:13:32,980
♪Yet something drags me deeper♪

233
00:13:32,980 --> 00:13:37,020
♪Outwit the world but not the way we meet♪

234
00:13:37,020 --> 00:13:41,700
♪Splendid blooms line deadly ground♪

235
00:13:45,620 --> 00:13:49,020
♪Life's a phantom, yet I find you♪

236
00:13:49,020 --> 00:13:52,380
♪In a world of lies, you're all that's clear♪

237
00:13:52,380 --> 00:13:54,860
♪I know how this story ends♪

238
00:13:54,860 --> 00:13:59,020
♪I still want what's in your eyes♪

239
00:13:59,020 --> 00:14:02,300
♪When it's over and I'm gone♪

240
00:14:02,300 --> 00:14:06,100
♪Please forget me and move on♪

241
00:14:06,100 --> 00:14:12,340
♪Just let this absurd dream fade♪

242
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:23,860
♪Snow hides our tracks♪

243
00:14:27,420 --> 00:14:37,140
♪When do I finally wake♪
